						<summary>

						<p>On a slab lying in front of the Rāmēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1545 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 146[7], Viśvāvasu, Āśvīja śu. 15,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1545 A.D., September 20, (Sunday).</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers the grant of wet and dry lands for offerings and a perpetual lamp in the temple of Rāmayadēva at Yeraguḍi by Bhūpatirāya, the agent of Kṛishṇappa-nāyaka. Yaraguḍi is stated to be situated in Būdigumma-sīma held as <hi rend="italic">amara</hi> by the donor.</p>						

						</summary>
